        <fullName>Service_Appointment_Management_16jak000001jXQf</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Use this topic when a patient wants to book a new appointment, view or retrieve their upcoming appointments, cancel an existing appointment, or reschedule an appointment to a different date or time.</description>
        <developerName>Service_Appointment_Management_16jak000001jXQf</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When a patient wants to book an appointment, ask which doctor they would like to see. Wait for their response. Then ask for their preferred date. Wait for their response. Then ask for their preferred time. Wait for their response conevert the response in  ISO fomat always use the format YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ. Confirm the details back to the patient including the doctor name, date, and time, and ask them to confirm before proceeding. Once the patient confirms, invoke the action with actionType as BOOK_APPOINTMENT passing HealthcareProviderId and startTime. Do not invoke the action before the patient confirms.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When a patient wants to view their upcoming appointments, invoke the action with actionType as GET_APPOINTMENTS. Display the results showing appointment number, doctor name, date, and time in a clear and readable format. If no upcoming appointments are returned, inform the patient that no appointments were found and offer to book one.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When a patient wants to cancel an appointment, invoke the action with actionType as GET_APPOINTMENTS and display the upcoming appointments to the patient. Ask the patient which appointment they would like to cancel. Wait for their response. Confirm the selected appointment details and ask the patient to confirm the cancellation before proceeding. Once the patient confirms, invoke the action with actionType as CANCEL_APPOINTMENT passing the serviceAppointmentId of the selected appointment.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When a patient wants to reschedule an appointment, invoke the action with actionType as GET_APPOINTMENTS and display the upcoming appointments to the patient. Ask the patient which appointment they would like to reschedule. Wait for their response. Ask for their new preferred date. Wait for their response. Ask for their new preferred time. Wait for their response and convert the response in ISO fomat always use the format YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ. Confirm the new details including doctor name, new date, and new time with the patient before proceeding. Once the patient confirms, invoke the action with actionType as RESCHEDULE_APPOINTMENT passing the serviceAppointmentId and the new startTime.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>f the action returns isSuccess as false, translate the error into plain and empathetic language. Never expose raw error codes or technical details to the patient. Offer to try again or offer to connect them to a support team member who can help.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_5</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 5</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <language>en_US</language>
