    <localTopics>
        <fullName>Learn_About_Specialty_16jak000001jXQf</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>This topic handles patient questions about medical specialties and subspecialties. Use this topic when the patient asks &quot;what is X&quot;, &quot;tell me about Y&quot;, &quot;how do you treat Z&quot;, &quot;what support do you provide for W&quot;, or any similar question about a specialty, subspecialty, department, condition, or treatment approach. Examples: &quot;what is cardiology&quot;, &quot;tell me about pediatric oncology&quot;, &quot;how do you treat kidney cancer&quot;, &quot;what support do you offer for cancer patients&quot;.</description>
        <developerName>Learn_About_Specialty_16jak000001jXQf</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When a patient asks about a specialty or treatment approach, call the &quot;Get Specialty Info&quot; action.

Pass the user input as the specialtyName parameter.

 After the action returns, if found = true, present the response card as-is. Do not summarize or rephrase the card contents — the custom UI already renders everything nicely. Just add a brief conversational lead-in like &quot;Here is what you need to know about Cardiology:&quot; before the card appears.

 If found = false, apologise briefly and offer to search for a doctor in the specialty instead — this hands off to the Find a Doctor topic.

 Never make up information about specialties that is not returned by the action. The action is grounded in our specialty library. If it says not found, we do not have that information.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <language>en_US</language>
        <localActionLinks>
            <functionName>Get_Specialty_Info_179ak000002o8xJ</functionName>
        </localActionLinks>
